1
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,333
( chorus vocalizing )

2
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,666
Narrator: NEN ABILITIES

3
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,800
FALL INTO THE FOLLOWING
SIX DISTINCT CATEGORIES.

4
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:18,500
ENHANCERS ARE ABLE
TO STRENGTHEN AND REINFORCE

5
00:00:18,566 --> 00:00:22,233
THE NATURAL PROPERTIES
OF ANY OBJECT THEY ENCOUNTER.

6
00:00:22,266 --> 00:00:24,400
TRANSMUTERS CAN MANIPULATE

7
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:27,900
AND CHANGE
THE QUALITY OF AURA AT WILL.

8
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:31,600
SIMILAR TO TRANSMUTERS,
CONJURERS HAVE THE ABILITY

9
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:35,400
TO MATERIALIZE AN OBJECT
OUT OF AURA.

10
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:38,133
EMITTERS CAN PROPEL THEIR AURA,

11
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:41,133
SHOOTING OR
PROJECTING IT FORWARD.

12
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:43,600
MANIPULATORS CAN USE THEIR AURA

13
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:46,966
TO CONTROL OBJECTS
OR LIVING THINGS.

14
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,500
SPECIALISTS POSSESS
RARE ABILITIES

15
00:00:49,566 --> 00:00:53,333
WHICH DO NOT FIT WITHIN
THE OTHER FIVE CATEGORIES.

16
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:57,100
ONE MUST DETERMINE WHICH
CATEGORY THEIR AURA FALLS INTO.

17
00:00:57,133 --> 00:01:01,973
THIS IS THE FIRST STEP
TO BECOMING A SKILLED NEN USER.

18
00:01:02,006 --> 00:01:03,940
♪

19
00:01:07,506 --> 00:01:10,440
( singing in Japanese )

20
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:26,146
Gon: AUNT MITO!

21
00:02:26,537 --> 00:02:30,103
SO LONG! I'M GONNA GO
FIND GING! I PROMISE!

22
00:02:30,137 --> 00:02:31,103
Woman: BYE!

23
00:02:31,137 --> 00:02:32,870
Gon: AND AFTER I MEET HIM,

24
00:02:32,870 --> 00:02:35,003
I'M GONNA COME BACK
TO THE ISLAND, OKAY?

25
00:02:35,037 --> 00:02:36,870
‐ Woman: GOOD LUCK TO YOU.
‐ Man: SAFE TRIP.

26
00:02:36,937 --> 00:02:39,370
Gon: BYE! TAKE CARE!

27
00:02:39,437 --> 00:02:42,137
I'LL MISS YOU!

28
00:02:42,170 --> 00:02:44,870
( overlapping chatter )

29
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:46,837
( waves crash )

30
00:02:51,703 --> 00:02:54,170
Narrator: MEANWHILE,
AS GON AND KILLUA

31
00:02:54,203 --> 00:02:55,770
DEPART FROM WHALE ISLAND,

32
00:02:55,803 --> 00:03:00,377
KURAPIKA IS PREPARING
TO BEGIN A JOURNEY OF HIS OWN.

33
00:03:02,510 --> 00:03:04,277
Kurapika: SO YOU REMEMBER ME?

34
00:03:04,310 --> 00:03:05,710
Agent: WELL, YEAH.

35
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:08,310
WE DON'T GET
MANY VISITORS HERE.

36
00:03:08,343 --> 00:03:10,843
IN FACT, EVER SINCE
YOU WERE HERE LAST,

37
00:03:10,877 --> 00:03:13,677
THERE'S ONLY BEEN
ONE OTHER PERSON.

38
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:18,810
THIS PLACE IS A WHOLE LOT HARDER
TO FIND THAN YOU THINK.

39
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:24,610
♪

40
00:03:24,643 --> 00:03:26,977
YOU FOUND THIS AGENCY
ON YOUR OWN,

41
00:03:27,010 --> 00:03:29,610
AND THAT TELLS ME
YOU'RE PRETTY SHARP.

42
00:03:30,477 --> 00:03:31,777
EVEN SO...

43
00:03:31,810 --> 00:03:34,277
I CAN'T INTRODUCE YOU
TO OUR VALUED CLIENTS.

44
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:37,543
AND IT'S NOT BECAUSE OF
YOUR TOTAL LACK OF EXPERIENCE.

45
00:03:37,543 --> 00:03:40,210
SOME OF OUR CLIENTS
DON'T SEEM TO MIND THAT.

46
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:43,877
THE THING IS,
EXPERIENCE ISN'T ALL YOU LACK.

47
00:03:43,877 --> 00:03:45,710
Kurapika: BUT WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

48
00:03:45,777 --> 00:03:48,710
LIKE I TOLD YOU, I ALREADY
HAVE A HUNTER'S LICENSE.

49
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:51,277
Agent: MAYBE,
BUT YOUR EXAM ISN'T OVER YET.

50
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:52,277
( Kurapika gasps )

51
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:54,477
Agent: IT'S OBVIOUS.

52
00:03:54,510 --> 00:03:56,377
Kurapika: EXCUSE ME?

53
00:04:00,043 --> 00:04:01,117
( aura sneers )

54
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:04,050
Agent: YOU CAN'T SEE ANYTHING,
CAN YOU?

55
00:04:04,117 --> 00:04:05,717
( Kurapika stammers )

56
00:04:06,717 --> 00:04:09,017
Agent: YOU COME BACK
WHEN YOU CAN.

57
00:04:10,483 --> 00:04:13,050
( wind blows )

58
00:04:19,517 --> 00:04:21,117
( Kurapika exhales )

59
00:04:22,217 --> 00:04:23,517
( gasps )

60
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:36,716
Man: YOU CAN'T SEE IT,
BUT YOU CAN SENSE IT, HUH?

61
00:04:36,783 --> 00:04:38,716
Kurapika: WHY DID YOU DO THAT?!

62
00:04:38,783 --> 00:04:40,317
Man: THIS? ( chuckles )

63
00:04:40,350 --> 00:04:42,117
I WAS JUST PLAYING AROUND.

64
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,183
( thunder crashes )

65
00:04:43,217 --> 00:04:44,817
THIS MUST BE FATE,

66
00:04:44,850 --> 00:04:46,950
US CROSSING PATHS. YOU THINK?

67
00:04:46,983 --> 00:04:48,217
TRY TO THINK OF THIS

68
00:04:48,217 --> 00:04:51,550
AS A LITTLE BIT OF
FRIENDLY ADVICE FROM A SENIOR.

69
00:04:51,550 --> 00:04:53,950
( Kurapika gasps )

70
00:04:53,983 --> 00:04:56,783
Man: YOU DIDN'T NOTICE
WHEN I STOLE THIS

71
00:04:56,817 --> 00:04:59,350
OR WHEN I WALKED
RIGHT PAST YOU, EITHER.

72
00:04:59,383 --> 00:05:00,950
YOU'RE TOTALLY CLUELESS.

73
00:05:00,983 --> 00:05:04,723
Kurapika: BASTARD. GIVE ME
BACK MY LICENSE RIGHT NOW!

74
00:05:04,790 --> 00:05:08,690
Man: DOES A NEWBIE
WHO KNOWS NOTHING OF NEN

75
00:05:08,723 --> 00:05:11,357
HAVE A CHANCE OF BEATING ME?

76
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,890
Kurapika: NEN, HUH?

77
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:16,890
‐ ( man chuckles )
‐ ( thunder crashes )

78
00:05:18,557 --> 00:05:20,990
WANNA GIVE IT A TRY?

79
00:05:28,223 --> 00:05:30,190
( Kurapika panting )

80
00:05:32,190 --> 00:05:33,957
Man: DO YOU GET IT NOW?

81
00:05:33,990 --> 00:05:36,690
THERE'S SOMETHING IMPORTANT
YOU STILL LACK.

82
00:05:39,290 --> 00:05:41,523
COME WITH ME.

83
00:05:43,557 --> 00:05:45,557
I'LL TEACH YOU.

84
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:51,690
THE REAL EXAM HAS JUST BEGUN.

85
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:58,123
( birds chirping )

86
00:06:02,163 --> 00:06:04,297
TODAY WE'RE GONNA DETERMINE

87
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:06,897
WHICH CATEGORY
YOUR AURA FALLS UNDER.

88
00:06:16,563 --> 00:06:18,897
( Kurapika exhales )

89
00:06:28,997 --> 00:06:32,463
Teacher: THERE'S SOMETHING
FORMING IN THE WATER,

90
00:06:32,497 --> 00:06:35,063
SO YOU'RE A CONJURER.
IT'S CLEAR.

91
00:06:36,697 --> 00:06:38,163
Kurapika: A CONJURER?

92
00:06:38,197 --> 00:06:41,297
Teacher: A TYPE WHOSE SPECIALTY
IS MANIFESTING THEIR AURA.

93
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:45,030
Kurapika: I SEE. I WAS HOPING
I WOULD BE AN ENHANCER.

94
00:06:45,063 --> 00:06:48,163
Teacher: UNFORTUNATELY YOU CAN'T
CHANGE WHAT YOU'RE BORN WITH.

95
00:06:48,197 --> 00:06:49,797
BUT IT ISN'T HOPELESS.

96
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:51,963
YOU CAN STILL LEARN
ENHANCEMENT TECHNIQUES.

97
00:06:51,997 --> 00:06:56,063
AND THAT WOULD MAKE AN EXCELLENT
TOPIC FOR US TO GO OVER TODAY.

98
00:06:56,130 --> 00:06:58,963
( wings flutter )

99
00:06:58,997 --> 00:07:01,703
NOW LET'S SAY
YOU HAVE THE APTITUDE

100
00:07:01,737 --> 00:07:05,870
TO ACHIEVE 100% MASTERY
OF CONJURATION ABILITIES.

101
00:07:05,903 --> 00:07:09,903
AT THE MOST, THIS IS HOW MUCH
YOU COULD MASTER THE OTHERS.

102
00:07:11,203 --> 00:07:14,903
IT DOESN'T MATTER
HOW FAST OF A LEARNER YOU ARE.

103
00:07:14,903 --> 00:07:18,237
YOU CAN NEVER COMPLETELY MASTER
A DIFFERENT CATEGORY.

104
00:07:18,303 --> 00:07:22,737
THE FURTHER A CATEGORY IS FROM
YOUR OWN, THE LESS YOU ACQUIRE.

105
00:07:22,803 --> 00:07:25,403
Kurapika: WHY IS
SPECIALIST AT ZERO?

106
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,637
Teacher: SPECIALIST IS
A UNIQUE CATEGORY,

107
00:07:27,670 --> 00:07:29,637
AND THEIR ABILITIES
AREN'T THE KIND

108
00:07:29,670 --> 00:07:30,970
YOU CAN SIMPLY TEACH YOURSELF.

109
00:07:31,003 --> 00:07:33,303
THEY'RE VERY DISTINCT ABILITIES,

110
00:07:33,337 --> 00:07:35,703
EITHER INHERITED
OR ACQUIRED NATURALLY,

111
00:07:35,737 --> 00:07:38,137
A PRODUCT OF YOUR ENVIRONMENT.

112
00:07:38,170 --> 00:07:40,037
SO WHY THIS POSITION?

113
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:43,803
BECAUSE THE ADJACENT CATEGORIES,
CONJURER AND MANIPULATOR,

114
00:07:43,837 --> 00:07:47,170
HAVE THE GREATEST CHANCE OF
BECOMING SPECIALISTS LATER ON.

115
00:07:47,203 --> 00:07:52,370
IN THAT RESPECT, YOU STILL
HAVE A CHANCE, IN A WAY.

116
00:07:52,403 --> 00:07:55,203
DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT YOU SAID?

117
00:07:55,237 --> 00:07:56,203
♪

118
00:07:56,237 --> 00:07:59,370
( Kurapika panting )

119
00:07:59,403 --> 00:08:03,743
‐ Teacher: HMM?
‐ Kurapika: I‐‐I NEED‐‐

120
00:08:03,743 --> 00:08:06,910
I NEED ENOUGH POWER
TO FIGHT ON MY OWN!

121
00:08:16,010 --> 00:08:19,010
Teacher: YOU MIGHT ASSUME THAT
THE FASTEST MEANS TO YOUR GOAL

122
00:08:19,043 --> 00:08:21,343
WOULD BE THROUGH
ENHANCEMENT ABILITIES,

123
00:08:21,377 --> 00:08:22,743
AND YOU'D BE RIGHT.

124
00:08:22,810 --> 00:08:24,977
ENHANCERS ARE ABLE TO REINFORCE

125
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:29,377
OFFENSE, DEFENSE, AND HEALING
MOST EFFICIENTLY.

126
00:08:29,410 --> 00:08:31,743
BUT SINCE YOU'RE A CONJURER,

127
00:08:31,810 --> 00:08:36,377
YOU CAN ONLY LEARN ENHANCER
ABILITIES UP TO HALF POTENCY.

128
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:38,643
IF YOU TRY
TO EXCEED YOUR LIMITS,

129
00:08:38,677 --> 00:08:40,643
IT WILL CAUSE YOU
INCREDIBLE STRAIN,

130
00:08:40,677 --> 00:08:42,377
AND THAT CAN WEAKEN YOU.

131
00:08:42,410 --> 00:08:43,377
( snap )

132
00:08:43,410 --> 00:08:45,910
IT COULD EVEN BE FATAL.

133
00:08:47,210 --> 00:08:51,243
CONSISTENT POWER
IS THE ONLY WAY TO STAY ON TOP.

134
00:08:51,243 --> 00:08:54,177
Kurapika: IF I WERE CONSISTENT
IN MY ABILITIES AS A CONJURER,

135
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:57,077
DO YOU THINK THAT IT
WOULD HELP ME IN A BATTLE

136
00:08:57,143 --> 00:09:00,077
IF I WERE PITTED
AGAINST A MASTER ENHANCER?

137
00:09:00,077 --> 00:09:01,550
Teacher: HMM.

138
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:04,250
IN SHORT,
IT WOULD BE DIFFICULT.

139
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,550
WHEN CLOSELY COMPARED

140
00:09:05,583 --> 00:09:07,750
TO AN ENHANCER'S
OFFENSE AND DEFENSE,

141
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:09,483
FAR MORE OFTEN THAN NOT,

142
00:09:09,517 --> 00:09:11,883
CONJURERS ARE SIMPLY
NOT AS EVENLY BALANCED.

143
00:09:11,917 --> 00:09:15,383
BUT THAT SAID, YOU COULD
ACTUALLY BE QUITE FORMIDABLE

144
00:09:15,417 --> 00:09:17,017
IF YOU FIND YOUR GROOVE.

145
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:20,683
‐ HERE'S A QUIZ.
‐ Kurapika: EH?

146
00:09:20,717 --> 00:09:22,683
Teacher: CAN YOU
CONJURE A SWORD

147
00:09:22,717 --> 00:09:25,083
THAT'S ABLE
TO CUT THROUGH ANYTHING?

148
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:27,883
‐ Kurapika: YOU CAN'T.
‐ Teacher: WHY NOT?

149
00:09:27,917 --> 00:09:31,650
Kurapika: BECAUSE IT EXCEEDS
THE BOUNDS OF HUMAN CAPACITY.

150
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:34,483
Teacher: THAT'S EXACTLY RIGHT.

151
00:09:34,517 --> 00:09:36,750
THERE ARE THINGS
YOU CAN NEVER CONJURE,

152
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:39,817
EVEN WITH 100% MASTERY.

153
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:41,150
♪

154
00:09:41,183 --> 00:09:42,683
OF COURSE, YOU COULD CONJURE

155
00:09:42,717 --> 00:09:44,917
A SWORD THAT'S
VERY SHARP AND STURDY,

156
00:09:44,983 --> 00:09:47,517
BUT IT WOULD MAKE
A LOT MORE SENSE

157
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:49,483
TO JUST GO OUT AND BUY ONE.

158
00:09:49,517 --> 00:09:51,917
YOU WOULDN'T NEED
EXTRA TRAINING.

159
00:09:51,983 --> 00:09:56,017
YOU CAN MAKE THE SWORD APPEAR
AND DISAPPEAR USING NEN,

160
00:09:56,050 --> 00:09:58,750
BUT CONJURED WEAPONS
JUST AREN'T AS EFFECTIVE.

161
00:09:58,817 --> 00:10:00,483
THE PHYSICAL VERSIONS
ARE BETTER.

162
00:10:00,517 --> 00:10:04,690
UNFORTUNATELY YOU CAN'T CONJURE
ANYTHING THAT'S SUPERNATURAL.

163
00:10:04,757 --> 00:10:06,823
SO CONSIDER IT CAREFULLY,

164
00:10:06,857 --> 00:10:09,290
AND CHOOSE
WHAT YOU WISH TO CONJURE.

165
00:10:09,323 --> 00:10:10,990
NO MISTAKES ALLOWED.

166
00:10:11,023 --> 00:10:14,423
CONJURING SOMETHING AT WILL
TAKES A LOT OF CONCENTRATION,

167
00:10:14,457 --> 00:10:16,690
NOT TO MENTION
TRAINING AND TIME,

168
00:10:16,757 --> 00:10:19,923
AND THAT'S JUST
WHAT IT TAKES FOR ONE THING.

169
00:10:19,957 --> 00:10:21,257
♪

170
00:10:21,290 --> 00:10:23,090
Agent: WHAT A SURPRISE.

171
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:24,157
Kurapika: HUH?

172
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,423
Agent: I DON'T KNOW MANY PEOPLE

173
00:10:25,457 --> 00:10:27,623
WHO LEARNED NEN
IN ONLY SIX MONTHS.

174
00:10:27,657 --> 00:10:31,590
SO WHAT KIND OF EMPLOYER
DO YOU WANT?

175
00:10:33,023 --> 00:10:36,790
Hisoka: I'LL TELL YOU SOMETHING
INTERESTING ABOUT SPIDERS.

176
00:10:36,823 --> 00:10:39,790
♪

177
00:10:39,823 --> 00:10:45,423
MEET ME IN YORKNEW CITY
ON SEPTEMBER FIRST.

178
00:10:45,457 --> 00:10:47,957
Kurapika: I WOULD PREFER
TO FIND AN EMPLOYER

179
00:10:47,990 --> 00:10:50,357
WITH STRONG TIES
TO THE YORKNEW AUCTION.

180
00:10:50,357 --> 00:10:52,623
THE JOB IS IRRELEVANT.

181
00:10:52,657 --> 00:10:55,157
Agent: THE YORKNEW CITY AUCTION.

182
00:10:57,257 --> 00:10:59,823
EMPLOYERS WHO HAVE
A LOT OF INFLUENCE

183
00:10:59,857 --> 00:11:02,363
GENERALLY POST
THE DIFFICULT JOBS.

184
00:11:02,363 --> 00:11:07,363
I DOUBT THEY'RE LOOKING TO HIRE
A HUNTER WITH ZERO EXPERIENCE.

185
00:11:08,463 --> 00:11:09,830
I SEE THREE,

186
00:11:09,863 --> 00:11:11,797
THREE EMPLOYERS WHO'LL DECIDE

187
00:11:11,830 --> 00:11:14,297
BASED ON THE INTERVIEW
AND NOT ON YOUR RECORD,

188
00:11:14,330 --> 00:11:17,830
AND IT LOOKS LIKE ALL THREE
ARE LOOKING FOR BODYGUARDS.

189
00:11:17,863 --> 00:11:20,630
I'LL READ. YOU CHOOSE, 'KAY?

190
00:11:20,663 --> 00:11:23,430
THE FIRST IS A HANDGUN BUFF.

191
00:11:23,463 --> 00:11:25,597
HE'S AFTER
THE MISETTE LIMITED EDITION

192
00:11:25,630 --> 00:11:29,830
BULL SNAKE MODEL S‐55,
NUMBER 001.

193
00:11:29,863 --> 00:11:32,763
THE SECOND IS
A COLLECTOR OF FINE CHINA.

194
00:11:32,797 --> 00:11:35,363
THIS ONE IS SEEKING
RODO MEMORIAL PLATES

195
00:11:35,430 --> 00:11:39,030
FROM 1655 TO 1657.

196
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:42,130
AND THE THIRD
IS A FLESH COLLECTOR...

197
00:11:42,163 --> 00:11:43,630
( Kurapika gasps )

198
00:11:43,663 --> 00:11:47,663
SEEKING A HIDE WITH A FULL
BODY TATTOO OF A RISING DRAGON,

199
00:11:47,697 --> 00:11:50,097
THE HEAD OF A CHILD
WITH JELLY SYNDROME,

200
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:51,630
AND A FEW OTHERS.

201
00:11:51,663 --> 00:11:53,763
THAT SURE IS QUITE A HOBBY.

202
00:11:53,797 --> 00:11:55,830
ALL RIGHT. TAKE YOUR PICK.

203
00:11:55,863 --> 00:11:56,830
HUH?

204
00:11:56,863 --> 00:11:58,330
♪

205
00:11:58,363 --> 00:11:59,630
Teacher: CHAINS?

206
00:11:59,663 --> 00:12:02,670
Kurapika: YES. WHEN YOU
SAID I WAS A CONJURER,

207
00:12:02,703 --> 00:12:05,670
THAT WAS THE FIRST THING
THAT CAME TO MIND.

208
00:12:05,703 --> 00:12:08,203
Teacher: INTERESTING,
BUT WHY CHAINS?

209
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:10,537
Kurapika: IT'S BECAUSE
THERE ARE SOME PEOPLE

210
00:12:10,537 --> 00:12:12,803
AT LARGE IN THE WORLD
RIGHT NOW

211
00:12:12,837 --> 00:12:15,537
WHO NEED TO BE CHAINED TO HELL.

212
00:12:16,603 --> 00:12:18,437
Teacher: OH, IS THAT SO?

213
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:20,970
BECAUSE I CAN'T SHAKE
THE NAGGING SUSPICION

214
00:12:21,003 --> 00:12:23,770
THAT YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO'LL BE CHAINED DOWN.

215
00:12:23,803 --> 00:12:26,037
Kurapika: WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU KNOW?

216
00:12:26,037 --> 00:12:28,503
Teacher: WAIT A SECOND!
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

217
00:12:28,537 --> 00:12:30,337
I'M YOUR TEACHER! DO AS I SAY!

218
00:12:30,370 --> 00:12:32,203
I'M NOT DONE TALKING TO YOU!

219
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:33,603
HOLD ON, DAMN IT!

220
00:12:34,770 --> 00:12:37,937
LIKE I TOLD YOU,
ORDINARY CHAINS ARE POINTLESS!

221
00:12:37,970 --> 00:12:39,003
THEY'RE INFERIOR!

222
00:12:39,037 --> 00:12:42,037
AND CONJURING SOME KIND
OF UNBREAKABLE CHAIN

223
00:12:42,103 --> 00:12:43,770
IS COMPLETELY IMPOSSIBLE!

224
00:12:43,803 --> 00:12:45,837
♪

225
00:12:54,303 --> 00:12:56,703
Kurapika: ON SEPTEMBER FIRST,

226
00:12:56,770 --> 00:13:00,677
YORKNEW CITY WILL HOST
THE WORLD'S GREATEST AUCTION.

227
00:13:00,710 --> 00:13:03,443
THAT'S WHERE THE SPIDER,

228
00:13:03,477 --> 00:13:05,877
THE PHANTOM TROUPE WILL APPEAR.

229
00:13:05,877 --> 00:13:07,477
( chains jangle )

230
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:09,610
( woman gasps )

231
00:13:13,543 --> 00:13:15,377
THAT HEARTBEAT,

232
00:13:15,443 --> 00:13:18,377
IT PLAYS
A HORRIBLE MELODY OF RAGE.

233
00:13:29,807 --> 00:13:33,140
Agent: SO YOU WANT ME
TO FIND YOU AN EMPLOYER

234
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:35,107
WITH CONNECTIONS
TO THE YORKNEW AUCTION?

235
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:36,807
DID I GET THAT RIGHT?

236
00:13:36,873 --> 00:13:37,807
Hunter: THAT'S RIGHT.

237
00:13:37,807 --> 00:13:40,073
Agent: LIKE THE LAST GUY
WHO WALKED IN.

238
00:13:40,107 --> 00:13:41,073
Hunter: HUH?

239
00:13:41,107 --> 00:13:43,307
Agent: SAME REQUEST TWICE TODAY.

240
00:13:43,307 --> 00:13:45,473
AMUSING, IS ALL.

241
00:13:45,473 --> 00:13:47,407
Hunter: THE BOY I JUST PASSED?

242
00:13:48,307 --> 00:13:50,373
Agent: DO YOU KNOW HIM?

243
00:13:50,407 --> 00:13:52,640
Hunter: UH, NO, I DON'T.

244
00:13:52,707 --> 00:13:54,273
( chains jangle )

245
00:13:54,307 --> 00:13:56,807
HE'S INTERESTED
IN THE AUCTION, TOO?

246
00:13:57,940 --> 00:13:59,140
BUT THEN...

247
00:13:59,140 --> 00:14:02,647
WHY IS HIS HEARTBEAT
SO FULL OF RAGE?

248
00:14:02,713 --> 00:14:04,647
♪

249
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,780
( car door closes )

250
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:24,147
( man gasps )

251
00:14:26,647 --> 00:14:28,713
( whimpers )

252
00:14:28,747 --> 00:14:30,647
Man #2: EATING WITH
A TWERP LIKE THAT

253
00:14:30,647 --> 00:14:32,613
WILL ONLY MAKE
YOUR FOOD TASTE WORSE.

254
00:14:32,647 --> 00:14:36,047
Man #3: WHY DON'T YOU
LET US TAKE YOU OUT INSTEAD?

255
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:40,247
WE'LL SHOW YOU THE BEST NIGHT
OF YOUR LIFE, SWEETHEART.

256
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:42,413
Woman: THIS ISN'T A DATE,
UNFORTUNATELY.

257
00:14:42,447 --> 00:14:44,880
I'M IN THE MIDDLE OF A JOB.

258
00:14:44,913 --> 00:14:46,247
Man #3: A JOB? REALLY?

259
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,480
Woman: THIS IS
ACTUALLY MY EMPLOYER.

260
00:14:48,547 --> 00:14:51,147
HE'S HIRED ME AS HIS BODYGUARD.

261
00:14:51,213 --> 00:14:52,547
Man #2: BODYGUARD?

262
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:54,547
Man #3: YOU'VE GOTTA BE JOKING.

263
00:14:54,580 --> 00:14:56,880
A BABE LIKE YOU, A BODYGUARD?

264
00:14:56,913 --> 00:14:58,247
( men laugh )

265
00:14:58,280 --> 00:15:01,720
Man #2: I'D BE HAPPY
TO LET YOU GUARD MY BODY.

266
00:15:01,753 --> 00:15:03,153
( slurps )

267
00:15:03,153 --> 00:15:05,320
Woman: I DON'T GUARD UGLY MEN,

268
00:15:05,387 --> 00:15:06,753
BUT THANKS, ANYWAY.

269
00:15:06,787 --> 00:15:09,720
Man #2: WHO DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE TALKING TO?!

270
00:15:09,753 --> 00:15:10,653
SHUT YOUR‐‐

271
00:15:14,987 --> 00:15:16,320
( laughs )

272
00:15:16,387 --> 00:15:17,487
( woman, echoing )
INSTANT LOVER.

273
00:15:17,553 --> 00:15:19,453
INSTANT LOVER.
INSTANT LOVER.

274
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:22,553
EVERY SINGLE PERSON THAT I KISS

275
00:15:22,587 --> 00:15:24,720
BECOMES MY WILLING SLAVE.

276
00:15:24,753 --> 00:15:26,320
( man #2 panting )

277
00:15:26,387 --> 00:15:28,320
WHAT'S YOUR COMMAND, MISTRESS?

278
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:30,220
I LIVE TO SERVE YOU.

279
00:15:31,153 --> 00:15:33,720
Woman: BEAT THEM UP FOR ME.

280
00:15:33,753 --> 00:15:36,120
Man #2: YES, MA'AM! MY PLEASURE!

281
00:15:36,153 --> 00:15:37,120
( men stammer )

282
00:15:37,153 --> 00:15:39,120
( man #2 laughs )

283
00:15:39,153 --> 00:15:41,287
‐ ( blows landing )
‐ ( men grunting )

284
00:15:42,153 --> 00:15:44,720
( employer whimpers )

285
00:15:44,753 --> 00:15:47,220
( screams )

286
00:15:49,153 --> 00:15:51,453
( woman sighs ) HE RAN AWAY.

287
00:15:51,487 --> 00:15:54,620
AH, WELL. GUESS I'LL NEED
ANOTHER EMPLOYER.

288
00:15:54,653 --> 00:15:55,887
WHAT A PAIN.

289
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:57,820
♪

290
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:05,227
Man: A SPLENDID MOON.

291
00:16:05,260 --> 00:16:06,493
Guard: THERE HE IS!

292
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:07,927
Guard #2: WE'VE GOT YOU NOW!

293
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:10,327
Guard #3: HAND OVER
THE CORPSE SAMPLES YOU STOLE,

294
00:16:10,327 --> 00:16:11,327
NICE AND EASY!

295
00:16:11,327 --> 00:16:13,660
Thief: HMM? DON'T INTERRUPT,

296
00:16:13,727 --> 00:16:16,427
NOT MY WORK
AND NOT THIS SPLENDID MOON.

297
00:16:16,460 --> 00:16:17,927
( guard #2 groans )
THAT'S ENOUGH!

298
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,327
PUT YOUR HANDS UP!

299
00:16:19,327 --> 00:16:23,560
Thief: I WAS ON THE VERGE
OF ANOTHER MASTERFUL POEM,

300
00:16:23,593 --> 00:16:26,960
BUT YOU SPOILED THE MOMENT,
YOU IMBECILES!

301
00:16:28,993 --> 00:16:31,493
♪

302
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:35,293
( blows landing )

303
00:16:39,827 --> 00:16:44,436
"SPLENDID FULL MOON AND PURSUERS
AS CLUMSY AS A BABOON..."

304
00:16:45,981 --> 00:16:48,215
( growls ) THAT SUCKS.

305
00:16:55,115 --> 00:16:57,615
Man: YES, I KNOW, ELIZA.

306
00:16:57,648 --> 00:17:00,481
WELL, IF THIS JOB
WORKS OUT, I‐‐

307
00:17:00,481 --> 00:17:03,321
YEAH. THERE'S NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

308
00:17:03,321 --> 00:17:04,788
I'LL HANDLE IT. RIGHT.

309
00:17:04,821 --> 00:17:07,155
I'LL TAKE CARE OF YOU
AND THE DOGS.

310
00:17:07,221 --> 00:17:08,488
REALLY WON'T BE A PROBLEM,

311
00:17:08,488 --> 00:17:11,088
SO DON'T WORRY, ELIZA.

312
00:17:11,121 --> 00:17:13,821
BEAR WITH ME
A LITTLE WHILE LONGER.

313
00:17:13,888 --> 00:17:16,288
YEAH. IT'LL BE FINE.

314
00:17:16,321 --> 00:17:18,421
YOU CAN COUNT ON ME.

315
00:17:19,488 --> 00:17:21,421
♪

316
00:17:31,221 --> 00:17:32,155
( chains jangle )

317
00:17:32,221 --> 00:17:33,588
( doorbell chimes )

318
00:17:33,621 --> 00:17:36,321
Kurapika: I WAS SENT
BY THE EMPLOYMENT AGENCY!

319
00:17:36,321 --> 00:17:38,321
MY NAME IS KURAPIKA!

320
00:17:42,821 --> 00:17:44,755
( dog growling )

321
00:17:51,621 --> 00:17:55,621
Butler: WELCOME. WE'RE HAPPY
THAT YOU COULD JOIN US.

322
00:18:02,495 --> 00:18:05,661
IF YOU'D BE SO KIND
AS TO WAIT HERE.

323
00:18:05,728 --> 00:18:07,661
♪

324
00:18:27,128 --> 00:18:29,295
Butler: THANK YOU
FOR YOUR PATIENCE.

325
00:18:29,328 --> 00:18:31,761
IT SEEMS EVERYONE HAS ARRIVED,

326
00:18:31,795 --> 00:18:36,428
SO WE WILL NOW BEGIN GOING OVER
THE DETAILS OF THE CONTRACT.

327
00:18:38,495 --> 00:18:42,295
Employer: I'LL START
BY GOING OVER THE REQUIREMENTS.

328
00:18:42,328 --> 00:18:46,728
I WON'T ASK WHETHER OR NOT
YOU HAVE A LICENSE.

329
00:18:46,761 --> 00:18:52,495
MY ONLY CONCERN IS WHETHER YOU
CAN OBTAIN THE ITEMS WE SEEK.

330
00:18:52,495 --> 00:18:56,495
THE AUCTION, AS YOU ALL KNOW,
WILL BEGIN IN ONE MONTH.

331
00:18:56,495 --> 00:18:59,628
BEFORE THAT TIME, FIND ONE ITEM
FROM THE LIST PROVIDED,

332
00:18:59,661 --> 00:19:02,835
AND THEN BRING IT
SAFELY BACK HERE.

333
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:05,335
Butler: HERE YOU GO.

334
00:19:05,401 --> 00:19:08,901
THESE ARE THE DATA CARDS
YOU'RE ASSIGNED.

335
00:19:08,935 --> 00:19:11,235
♪

336
00:19:14,168 --> 00:19:15,501
( beep )

337
00:19:28,435 --> 00:19:30,401
( Kurapika gasps )

338
00:19:30,435 --> 00:19:32,335
♪

339
00:19:34,235 --> 00:19:36,735
( gasping )

340
00:19:38,235 --> 00:19:40,501
Poet: WHAT? SOMETHING WRONG?

341
00:19:40,568 --> 00:19:42,235
YOU LOOK A LITTLE PALE.

342
00:19:42,268 --> 00:19:45,168
AH. THE EYEBALLS
OF A KURTA, HUH?

343
00:19:45,235 --> 00:19:47,501
"DIFFICULTY LEVEL 'A.'

344
00:19:47,501 --> 00:19:50,268
"PRESERVE THE POSTMORTEM
SCARLET HUE AFTER DEATH.

345
00:19:50,301 --> 00:19:52,168
COMPLETE SET
WITH HEAD PREFERRED."

346
00:19:52,235 --> 00:19:53,768
YEAH, I'VE HEARD ABOUT THAT.

347
00:19:53,801 --> 00:19:56,235
THEIR EYES TURN RED
WHENEVER THEY'RE EXCITED.

348
00:19:56,268 --> 00:19:58,335
‐ YOU SEE, THE KURTA‐‐
‐ Kurapika: SHUT UP.

349
00:19:59,935 --> 00:20:01,508
THAT'S ENOUGH.

350
00:20:02,775 --> 00:20:05,441
Poet: HMM. HUMPH.

351
00:20:07,375 --> 00:20:10,241
Employer: I'LL SAY IT AGAIN.
ALL THAT'S REQUIRED

352
00:20:10,275 --> 00:20:13,341
IS ONE ITEM
FROM THE LIST YOU'VE BEEN GIVEN.

353
00:20:13,375 --> 00:20:15,941
IF YOU'RE SUCCESSFUL,
YOU'LL BE HIRED

354
00:20:15,941 --> 00:20:20,341
AND BEGIN YOUR TRAINING
IN SECURITY AND ACQUISITIONS.

355
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:24,108
WELL, THEN,
BEST OF LUCK TO YOU.

356
00:20:24,175 --> 00:20:26,608
Kurapika: I WILL PASS THIS TEST.

357
00:20:26,675 --> 00:20:30,108
FIRST I MUST INGRATIATE MYSELF
AND WIN THEIR TRUST.

358
00:20:30,175 --> 00:20:32,241
IN ALL LIKELIHOOD,

359
00:20:32,275 --> 00:20:35,041
THE MAN WE SAW
WAS NOT THE ACTUAL CLIENT,

360
00:20:35,075 --> 00:20:38,941
THUS ILLUSTRATING THE DISTANCE
BETWEEN THE CLIENT AND MYSELF.

361
00:20:38,941 --> 00:20:42,675
IT'S CRITICAL THAT I GET
AS CLOSE TO THEM AS POSSIBLE

362
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:45,108
UNTIL THEY EVENTUALLY
LET THEIR GUARD DOWN

363
00:20:45,175 --> 00:20:47,541
AND SHARE THEIR SECRETS.

364
00:20:47,575 --> 00:20:51,608
THERE ARE TWO THINGS
THAT COLLECTORS ALWAYS DESIRE.

365
00:20:51,675 --> 00:20:55,041
THE FIRST IS ANY ITEM
OF EXTREME RARITY.

366
00:20:55,075 --> 00:20:56,608
THE SECOND IS COLLEAGUES

367
00:20:56,608 --> 00:20:59,341
TO WHOM THEY CAN BRAG
ABOUT THEIR COLLECTION.

368
00:20:59,375 --> 00:21:03,381
HE MUST HAVE CONNECTIONS
TO OTHER FLESH COLLECTORS,

369
00:21:03,415 --> 00:21:06,681
THOSE WHO SHARE
THEIR DISGUSTING ACQUISITIONS,

370
00:21:06,715 --> 00:21:08,515
A NETWORK OF SCUM.

371
00:21:08,548 --> 00:21:13,948
I WILL INFILTRATE THEIR RANKS
AND ERADICATE THEM ALL.

372
00:21:13,948 --> 00:21:15,548
( lock rattles )

373
00:21:15,581 --> 00:21:17,781
Poet: HEY, IT WON'T OPEN.

374
00:21:17,781 --> 00:21:19,081
( screen whirs )

375
00:21:19,115 --> 00:21:21,348
Employer: I FORGOT
TO MENTION ONE THING.

376
00:21:21,381 --> 00:21:25,348
THE MINIMUM REQUIREMENT
FOR THE POSITION IS STRENGTH,

377
00:21:25,381 --> 00:21:28,715
ENOUGH STRENGTH
TO GET OUT OF THIS MANSION...

378
00:21:28,748 --> 00:21:30,881
WITH YOUR LIVES.

379
00:21:39,615 --> 00:21:40,581
( woman gasps )

380
00:21:45,048 --> 00:21:47,515
♪

381
00:21:48,581 --> 00:21:51,515
Narrator: KURAPIKA
PURSUES HIS QUEST

382
00:21:51,548 --> 00:21:55,048
TO AVENGE HIS BRETHREN
AND PUNISH THE PHANTOM TROUPE,

383
00:21:55,081 --> 00:21:59,755
AND RIGHT NOW HE IS PREPARING
TO ENTER A NEW BATTLEFIELD.

384
00:22:01,388 --> 00:22:03,521
( singing in Japanese )

385
00:23:11,295 --> 00:23:13,195
Gon: COMING UP, GON...

386
00:23:13,228 --> 00:23:14,228
Killua: AND KILLUA'S...

387
00:23:14,261 --> 00:23:15,728
Both: HUNTERPEDIA!

388
00:23:19,356 --> 00:23:21,189
‐ Gon: I'M GON.
‐ Killua: I'M KILLUA.

389
00:23:21,223 --> 00:23:22,856
Both: AND THIS IS
OUR HUNTERPEDIA!

390
00:23:22,856 --> 00:23:25,056
Gon: TODAY WE'RE INTRODUCING
MIZUKEN, KURAPIKA'S TEACHER.

391
00:23:25,089 --> 00:23:26,523
Killua: AND HE'S
AN EMITTER TYPE.

392
00:23:26,556 --> 00:23:29,189
Gon: I GUESS NEN USERS
ARE FATED TO MEET NEN TEACHERS.

393
00:23:29,223 --> 00:23:30,756
Killua: IT HAPPENED TO US.

394
00:23:30,789 --> 00:23:33,356
Both: MAYBE THAT'S WHY WE
MET EACH OTHER. IT'S FATE!

395
00:23:34,389 --> 00:23:36,356
♪

396
00:23:39,189 --> 00:23:41,189
Gon: NEXT TIME,
"NEN USERS UNITE?"

397
00:23:41,189 --> 00:23:45,356
Killua: HEY, GON, LET'S GO BREAK
SOME OF MILLUKI'S FIGURINES.

398
00:23:45,389 --> 00:23:47,689
Gon: COUNT ME IN
AS YOUR ACCOMPLICE.

